Type: Package
Package: LLMRcontent
Title: LLM-Assisted Content Analysis for the Social Sciences
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ali", "Sanaei", , "sanaei@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A workflow for content analysis with large language models that
    validates coded labels against held-out human labels, built on 'LLMR'. It
    links three stages. Coding turns a codebook and a sealed gold standard into
    error-corrected category prevalences. Robustness audits test whether a coded
    conclusion holds across the measurement multiverse of prompts, models, label
    orders, and temperatures, reporting changes in sign, rank, and conclusion
    stability. Archives turn the audit log of a study into a content-addressed,
    sealed replication record a reviewer can rerun. The report() output for each
    object states its measurement-error, fragility, and verifiability stance: a
    coding result is a measurement with known error, an audit is a fragility
    statement, and an archive is a verifiable record, not a claim of truth. An
    optional 'Shiny' GUI (run_content_studio()) runs the same workflow
    interactively.
